 and 15) by Janet Finch-Saunders AM and Lynne Neagle AM aim to prevent the Welsh Government from bringing section 1 into force until CPS guidance has been fully updated and pathways away from prosecution have been devised and agreed, reflecting the committee's recommendation for a public awareness campaign promoting understanding about the effect of the Bill on the abolition of the defense of reasonable punishment. This would help ensure natural justice and proportionate remedy or censure, while being mindful of the relationship between parents and children in each family.">
