e.&#10;3. To devise and agree on pathways away from prosecution before bringing this section into force, amendments 10 and 15 have been tabled by Janet Finch-Saunders AM and Lynne Neagle AM. These amendments prevent the Welsh Government from bringing section 1 into force until CPS guidance has been fully updated to take into account the change in the law and until pathways away from prosecution have been devised and agreed. This reflects recommendation 4 of the committee, ensuring that future governments are committed to delivering a public awareness campaign and promoting understanding about the effect of the Bill on the abolition for the defence of reasonable punishment.">
